Diagnosis. Adult (
Fig. 5
). Wingspan 13.0−15.0 mm. This species can be easily distinguished from its congeners by the broad median process of the transtilla abruptly narrowed from the distal 1 / 3 to the pointed apex and the valva with a row of short, slender spines in the male genitalia (
Fig. 9
); and by the corpus bursae without a sclerotized plate in the female genitalia (Fig. 12 ).
